//What is your desired compensation range? (Range meaning the least you're comfortable with to the most you think you're worth.)
$35,000 - 75,000

//When can you start?
Immediately, provided the receiving department is covered sufficiently.

//Do you have any planned vacations/absences in the next six months that we should know about?
Nothing planned.

//SparkFun is a dog-friendly environment. Are comfortable working aroung dogs? If you are a dog-owner, would you see yourself bringing dogs to work?
I love working with all the dogs at SparkFun. I have a black lab registered at SparkFun named Eli, though he doesn't make it in very often.

//The active developer keeps up on happenings in the world of development and technology. Where do you you get your news?
LinkedIn.com, PluralSight.com, and I'm on a few email mailing lists.

//The sane developer does things other than writing code. What else occupies your time?
Disc golf, golf-golf, sprite editing, 3D modeling, and gaming.

//The worldy developer is in touch with some form of culture (books, music, film, etc.). How do you go about feeding this part of your brain?
I follow a few TV series; The Walking Dead, Dark Matter, and The Expanse are my favorites.
Most of the books I read are game-dev related texts.

//Please critique any of the SparkFun websites. With influence over the SparkFun dev team what would you focus on improving?
As an insider I'd want to focus on Sparkle. It's a fantastic tool, but it has a lot of room for improvement, at least from an inventory perspective.
